flowchart TD
%% Mikado graph for the 0.15.0 contract-chain partial-order work.

%% Each numbered node is a commit-sized step. Arrows point from a goal to its
%% prerequisites — leaves (green) have no further prerequisites and are safe to
%% start with. Depth-first per Mikado: pick a leaf, finish it, commit, repeat.

%% Chain: preconditions ≤ postconditions ≤ invariants. `:checks` is orthogonal.
%% Constraints:
%%   - Compile-time: `:purge` of a lower kind ⇒ all higher kinds must also be `:purge`.
%%   - Runtime: `false` for a lower kind ⇒ all higher kinds are skipped.

    G(["**Goal**<br/>0.15.0 enforces partial order between contract kinds"])

    G --> S1[1. Compile-time chain validator in resolve_config/3]
    G --> S2[2. Fix existing fixtures/tests with newly-invalid combos]
    G --> S3[3. should_evaluate?/3 with chain context]
    G --> S4[4. Emission passes chain context at every call site]
    G --> S5[5. Runtime chain propagation logic]
    G --> S6[6. One-time per-process log when propagation fires]
    G --> S7[7. Tests for runtime propagation behaviour]
    G --> S8[8. Docs: README + FAQ + concurrency guide]
    G --> S9[9. CHANGELOG + version bump]

    S2 --> S1
    S4 --> S3
    S5 --> S3
    S5 --> S4
    S6 --> S5
    S7 --> S6
    S8 --> S1
    S8 --> S5
    S8 --> S6
    S9 --> S2
    S9 --> S7
    S9 --> S8

    classDef leaf fill:#e7f5e7,stroke:#2e7d32,stroke-width:2px;
    class S1,S3 leaf;

    style G fill:#90EE90
    style S1 fill:#90EE90
    style S2 fill:#90EE90
    style S3 fill:#90EE90
    style S4 fill:#90EE90
    style S5 fill:#90EE90
    style S6 fill:#90EE90
    style S7 fill:#90EE90
    style S8 fill:#90EE90
    style S9 fill:#90EE90
